Interface BlockList<T extends Block>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The expected attachment type
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BlockList.Single<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBlockList, AbstractNumberOperation.NumberOperationBlockList, AbstractSingleBlockList, MethodBlock.StringBlockList, MethodBlock.VariableBlockList, VariableBlock.StringBlockList, VariableBlock.VariableBlockList

    public interface BlockList<T extends Block>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>
    A list of blocks, this is used for attachable blocks

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  BlockList.Single<T extends Block>
      If the block is guaranteed to have only one attachment then the block should implement this instead of AttachableBlock.
